cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG 

The paper focuses on developing human-centered tools for coping with imperfect algorithms during medical decision making. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning algorithms for image retrieval (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) in the medical domain. The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to understand the needs of pathologists (cs.CL) and the evaluation of the tools using machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
